modules.description: Handles positioning and layout calculations for terminal images using the Kitty graphics protocol. Provides functions to convert integer coordinates into validated placement values and manage image alignment within terminal cells. Works directly with Kitty image data structures to enable precise rendering in terminal environments.

Handles image identifier creation and validation for terminal graphics operations. Works with integer values to produce validated image identifiers used in terminal rendering. Used when preparing and transmitting image data to Kitty-compatible terminals.

Handles image transmission and rendering in Kitty-compatible terminals using the terminal graphics protocol. Provides functions to send raw pixel data in RGB, RGBA, or PNG format, display or store images with positioning options, and delete images based on identifiers, placement, or screen coordinates. Used to embed and manipulate images directly within terminal sessions.
